This paper is primarily focused on improving the robustness of deep neural networks (DNNs) through adversarial training, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of spectral normalization, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to improve the performance of DNNs. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of adversarial attacks, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a regularization scheme based on spectral normalization, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, and cs.NE, in that order.
